  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Every patient with HCC (Hepato-Cellular Carcinoma) with main portal vein thrombosis will be
      screened for presence of large esophageal varices and will be randomized between
      non-selective beta blocker versus primary endoscopic variceal ligation. They will be followed
      to assess the rate of reduction of index bleed rate as well as survival difference between
      the groups.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
